					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287" rend="visible">
						<summary>The revised recension of Maimonides' Sefer mitsṿot in the Hebrew translation of <name type="person" role="translator">Solomon ben Joseph ibn ῾Ayyub</name>.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287">
							<locus from="1r" to="134v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Sefer mitsṿot </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר מצות</title>
							<note>
								<p>There is no translator's preface in the manuscript. </p>
								<p>Folios 68r-69r contain a list of the sixty indispensable mitsṿot in the wording of the Pentateuch, with their numbers in Sefer mitsṿot. The translator arranged these in four tables in his autograph. </p>
							</note>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/100185495">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/100185495" xml:lang="en">Maimonides, Moses, 1135-1204</persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/100185495" xml:lang="he">משה בן מימון, 1138-1204 </persName>
							</author>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<extent>134 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>220</height>
										<width>160</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>145</height>
										<width>95</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>134 folios (+ 3 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>14 quires: i-xiii10 (folio 1-129), xiv5 (folios 130-134). The first leaf of the first quire has been cancelled. </p>
									<p>Catchwords at the end of the quires, partly cut away. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>First leaves slightly injured.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 " ruledLines="25" writtenLines="25">
									<p>Uniform layout. Visible pricking and ruling with a hard-point object. </p>
									<p>Last line written outside the ruling. </p>
									<p>Marginal notes, occasionally mutilated in the trimming. </p>
									<p>Sections enumerated with Hebrew letters in larger characters. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Italian semi-cursive script of the 15th century. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
